Overview: In November 2021 Spain exported €29B and imported €34B, resulting in a negative trade balance of €4.98B. Between November 2020 and November 2021 the exports of Spain have increased by €4.95B (20.6%) from €24.1B to €29B, while imports increased by €9.25B (37.4%) from €24.8B to €34B.
Exports: The top exports of Spain are Cars ($34.5B), Refined Petroleum ($12.3B), Vehicle Parts ($10.6B), Packaged Medicaments ($9.95B), and Delivery Trucks ($6.07B), exporting mostly to France ($47.4B), Germany ($34.9B), Portugal ($25.8B), Italy ($25.5B), and United Kingdom ($22.1B).
In: 2019, Spain was the world's biggest importer of Locust beans, seaweed, sugar beet, cane, for food ($96.2M), Chamois Leather ($29.1M), and Chalk ($17.9M)
Imports: The top imports of Spain are Crude Petroleum ($27.8B), Cars ($21.6B), Vehicle Parts ($13.2B), Packaged Medicaments ($10B), and Petroleum Gas ($8.58B), importing mostly from Germany ($47.8B), France ($40.8B), China ($29.8B), Italy ($26.7B), and Netherlands ($16.5B).
Location: Spain borders Andorra, France, Morocco, Portugal, and Gibraltar by land and Algeriaand Italy by sea.
Trade: In November 2021, the top exports of Spain were Cars (€2.51B), Refined Petroleum (€1.31B), Packaged Medicaments (€866M), Vehicle Parts (€739M), and Blood, antisera, vaccines, toxins and cultures (€686M). In November 2021 the top imports of Spain were Crude Petroleum (€2.58B), Petroleum Gas (€1.46B), Cars (€1.19B), Vehicle Parts (€1.16B), and Blood, antisera, vaccines, toxins and cultures (€1.09B).
Origins: In November 2021 the exports of Spain were mainly from Barcelona (€5.7B), Madrid (€3.74B), Valencia (€1.54B), Pontevedra (€1.12B), and La Coruña (€1.1B), while imports destinations were mainly Madrid (€8.4B), Barcelona (€6.79B), Valencia (€1.8B), Tarragona (€1.5B), and Vizcaya (€1.17B).
Destinations: In November 2021, Spain exported mostly to France (€4.34B), Germany (€3.12B), Portugal (€2.38B), Italy (€2.35B), and United Kingdom (€1.76B), and imported mostly from China (€3.73B), Germany (€3.58B), France (€3.28B), Italy (€2.11B), and United States (€1.96B).
